    <a title="Victoria" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/115951-victoria"><img alt="Victoria" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/f_50x66-6a03a5c12233c941481992b82eea8d23.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/90812974?book_show_action=true">Feb 21, 2010</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Victoria" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Victoria" href="/user/show/115951-victoria">Victoria</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="did not like it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">did not like it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Hardcover 9780226359922" href="/book/show/146738.The_Autumn_of_the_Middle_Ages">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/115951-victoria?shelf=non-fiction">non-fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/115951-victoria?shelf=history">history</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/115951-victoria?shelf=comps-medieval">comps-medieval</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/115951-victoria?shelf=2010">2010</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/115951-victoria?shelf=history-medieval">history-medieval</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/115951-victoria?shelf=history-europe">history-europe</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer90812974" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1282632938655350171">Severely dated, conceptually stunted, and deeply methodologically flawed. Burckhardtian in its attempt to capture the &quot;mood&quot; of the late middle ages, but based on a number of false premises (primarily, that the Renaissance was in any way secular, and that it lacked continuity with the culture of the middle ages, which apparently decayed and actually <i>went away entirely</i>) that add up to a distorted and unhistorical picture of the era.</span>
  <span id="freeText1282632938655350171" style="display:none">Severely dated, conceptually stunted, and deeply methodologically flawed. Burckhardtian in its attempt to capture the "mood" of the late middle ages, but based on a number of false premises (primarily, that the Renaissance was in any way secular, and that it lacked continuity with the culture of the middle ages, which apparently decayed and actually <i>went away entirely</i>) that add up to a distorted and unhistorical picture of the era.</span>
